\section*{Mofiza: DIY Talking Robot from Recycled Materials}

\subsection*{Technological Principle: Embedded Control System}

This project is a perfect blend of \textbf{Recycled Materials} (Cardboard) and \textbf{Modern Electronics} (Arduino). The robot operates based on three main functional blocks:

1.  \textbf{Sensor Block}: Uses an Infrared (IR) or Ultrasonic sensor to detect presence.
2.  \textbf{Processing Block}: An Arduino Nano board reads sensor signals and triggers voice commands.
3.  \textbf{Audio Block}: DFPlayer Mini module reads .wav or .mp3 files from a Micro SD card and plays them through a speaker.

\subsection*{System Block Diagram}
\includegraphics[Mofiza Robot System Block Diagram]{/assets/images/projects/talking-robot-diagram.svg}

\subsection*{Material List}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Recycled Materials}: Old cardboard boxes, PVC pipes, plastic bottle caps.
    \item \textbf{Electronics}: Arduino Nano, DFPlayer Mini Module, Micro SD Card, IR Sensor, 8 Ohm Speaker.
    \item \textbf{Tools}: Hot glue gun, paper cutter, jumper wires.
\end{itemize}

\subsection*{Step-by-Step Instructions}
\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Frame Construction}: Cut and glue cardboard pieces to form the robot body (leave a hollow space for electronics).
    \item \textbf{Circuit Assembly}: Connect the IR sensor and DFPlayer module to the Arduino board according to the pinout diagram.
    \item \textbf{Code & Sound Upload}: Save greetings (e.g., "Hello", "How are you?") to the SD card and upload the logic code to the Arduino.
    \item \textbf{Final Touch}: Place the circuit inside the robot and decorate with aluminum foil for a metallic look.
\end{enumerate}

